Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.cs3733d18.teamS.data.Node

  • public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
    A Node is an entity to hold Node information. Nodes are the the pixel coordinates, and name of certain real world locations in the hospital.

            int y3d,
            boolean disabled)
        Constructs a node using its coordinate positions, its id, the floor the building its in, the long name, the abbreviated name, and the team assigned to the node area.
        Parameters:
        id - the node id.
        x - the 2d x coordinate.
        y - the 2d y coordinate.
        floor - the floor the node is on.
        bldg - the building the node is in.
        type - the type of node.
        lName - the full name of the node.
        sName - the abbreviated name of the node.
        team - the team assigned to the node.
        x3d - the 3d x coordinate.
        y3d - the 3d y coordinate.
        disabled - a boolean for whether or not the node is disabled.
